  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Logistics Senior Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Duties and Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Support logistics operations for loan, demo, and sample units.</li><li>Manage end-to-end logistics activities for B2B service and professional/medical equipment, ensuring service levels and operational targets are met.</li><li>Coordinate outbound logistics operations, including shipment planning and documentation.</li><li>Support trade documentation, including certificates of origin and export-related documents.</li><li>Provide guidance and advice to internal stakeholders on logistics best practices, operational processes, and compliance requirements.</li><li>Ensure compliance with international trade regulations, customs requirements, and internal policies.</li><li>Provide professional logistics advisory support for specialized shipments and business needs.</li><li>Monitor logistics performance, analyze operational data, and prepare regular performance reports.</li><li>Coordinate and manage relationships with internal stakeholders and external logistics service providers.</li><li>Drive continuous improvement initiatives and support logistics-related projects to enhance operational efficiency and service quality.</li><li>Perform other related duties as directed in accordance with company policies and procedures.</li></ul><p><strong>Qualifications /Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum 3–5 years of relevant experience in logistics, supply chain, or freight forwarding.</li><li>Experience in managing end-to-end logistics operations, including outbound/inbound shipments and trade compliance.  </li><li>Exposure to B2B operations, professional/medical equipment, or similar industries is preferred.</li></ul><p><strong>Knowledge & Skills:  </strong></p><ul><li>Good understanding of international shipping procedures, customs regulations, and trade documentation (e.g., certificates of origin, ATA Carnet).    </li><li>Familiarity with logistics processes, operational best practices, and regulatory compliance.  </li><li>Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, with ability to monitor KPIs and optimize operations. </li><li>Proficiency in Microsoft Office (Excel, Word, PowerPoint)</li></ul><p><strong>Competencies / Soft Skills:  </strong></p><ul><li>Strong coordination and stakeholder management skills.</li><li>Effective communication skills, both verbal and written.</li><li>Ability to work independently, manage multiple tasks, and meet deadlines.</li><li>Proactive, detail-oriented, and customer-service focused mindset.   </li><li>Able to support continuous improvement initiatives and contribute to projects.</li></ul>",
